data.title: Wombat 285 Sticks
data.meta_description: Is it a stick or is it a bat?  Depends on where you're from, but it's based on the classic Australian template, strong and solid with a grunty hook.  This stick/bat has a huge pass, great reach and tackle with the large hook and lots of surface area for knock-downs and close-quarters combat.  This is the mid-size Womba
data.text:
Is it a stick or is it a bat? Depends on where you're from, but it's based on the classic Australian template, strong and solid with a grunty hook. This stick/bat has a huge pass, great reach and tackle with the large hook and lots of surface area for knock-downs and close-quarters combat. This is the mid-size Wombat. Sold as a set, 1 white and 1 black.

Textured handle with nameplate and a thumb grip texture

Solid polyurethane plastic, fiberglass reinforced for extra strength

This variant of the Wombat is 285mm long

Textured passing faces give excellent grip on the puck when handling and passing

This version also has a textured bottom face for added grip when controlling the puck

Curved passing edges are smooth and reliable, very easy and quick to get a feel for your pass

Option to set your name into the handle

Tapered blade gives a solid sweetspot for big hits and slim profile for fast handspeed and quick skills

10 degree bevel to suit todays modern pucks like the Australian, Simms and the Uni2

Fully drillable and sandable for those who like to attach lanyards etc.

We now offer the option to print your name into the handle of your sticks! Sick of losing your sticks poolside? This label is set into the plastic and cannot be rubbed off. If you select this option please nominate the name or nickname you want to use in your order notes during checkout. Please limit to 8 characters maximum.

PLEASE NOTE This product requires manufacture time - this may be up to two weeks (plus shipping time)
